## Workload Profiles

| Profile | Class | Plan | Max threads | Max memory | Queue cap | NUMA policy |
|---|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---|
| `metadata_storm_dry_run` | `metadata_storm` | `dry_run` | 64 | 64.0 GB | 4096 | pin metadata shards to observed NUMA nodes; downgrade if unavailable |
| `append_fsync_dry_run` | `append_fsync` | `dry_run` | 64 | 48.0 GB | 2048 | co-locate WAL shard and fsync workers per NUMA node when observable |
| `mixed_read_write_dry_run` | `mixed_read_write` | `dry_run` | 96 | 96.0 GB | 8192 | reader shards prefer local NUMA memory; writers pin to owning shard node |
| `scrub_repair_overlap_dry_run` | `scrub_repair_overlap` | `dry_run` | 80 | 80.0 GB | 4096 | repair morsels stay on the NUMA node owning the block-group shard |
| `cache_pressure_dry_run` | `cache_pressure` | `dry_run` | 96 | 192.0 GB | 8192 | cache shards allocate from local NUMA node; cross-node fallback is logged |

